<TITLE> Woman arrested with alleged links to JMB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Joypurhat, Dec 24 (bdnews24.com)The Rapid Action Battalion arrested Ambia Begum in Joypurhat Sunday night, with alleged links to banned militant outfit Jamaatul Mujahideen Bangladesh, said RAB officers. Captain Zakir Hossain of RAB-5 told bdnews24.com that the RAB contingent raided Jangalia village in Shaghata upazila of Gaibandha Sunday, acting on a tip-off. They picked up the 55-year-old woman with a number of books dedicated to the cause of religious extremism, Zakir said. Ambia's husband Amjad Hossain was not at home during the raid. The arrestee was handed over to Shaghata police station and a case has been filed against Ambia under the Emergency Powers Rules, the RAB captain said. bdnews24.co
